# General Conventions

## Environment Variables

- Never hardcode API URLs or secrets
- Always use environment variables with `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` prefix for client-side access
- Store sensitive values in `.env.local` (never commit)
- Document all required env vars in `.env.example`

```typescript
// Good
const apiUrl = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL;

// Bad
const apiUrl = 'https://api.example.com';
```

## Component Patterns

### Loading States

```tsx
export function UserProfile({ userId }: { userId: string }): JSX.Element {
  const { data: user, isLoading, error } = useGetUserQuery(userId);

  if (isLoading) return <Skeleton />;
  if (error) return <ErrorMessage error={error} />;
  if (!user) return <EmptyState message="User not found" />;

  return <div>{user.name}</div>;
}
```

### Error Handling

```tsx
import { useToast } from '@/components/ui/use-toast';

export function UpdateProfileForm(): JSX.Element {
  const [updateUser] = useUpdateUserMutation();
  const { toast } = useToast();

  const handleSubmit = async (values: ProfileFormValues) => {
    try {
      await updateUser(values).unwrap();
      toast({ title: 'Profile updated successfully' });
    } catch (error) {
      toast({
        title: 'Error',
        description: 'Failed to update profile',
        variant: 'destructive',
      });
    }
  };

  return <Formik onSubmit={handleSubmit}>...</Formik>;
}
```

## URL State Management

- Use `nuqs` for URL search parameter state when needed
- Keep URL state minimal and focused on shareable/bookmarkable data

```typescript
import { useQueryState } from 'nuqs';

export function SearchResults(): JSX.Element {
  const [search, setSearch] = useQueryState('q');
  
  return <input value={search || ''} onChange={(e) => setSearch(e.target.value)} />;
}
```

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML elements
- Add ARIA labels where needed
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Test with screen readers
- Maintain proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Use proper contrast ratios

## Documentation

- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions
- Document props interfaces
- Keep README updated with setup instructions
- Document any non-obvious patterns or workarounds

## Git Workflow

### Conventional Commits

Use conventional commit format:
- `feat:` - New features
- `fix:` - Bug fixes
- `chore:` - Maintenance tasks
- `refactor:` - Code refactoring
- `docs:` - Documentation changes
- `test:` - Test additions or changes
- `style:` - Code style changes (formatting, etc.)

Examples:
```
feat: add user profile page
fix: resolve login redirect issue
chore: update dependencies
refactor: simplify form validation logic
docs: update README with deployment steps
test: add smoke test for dashboard
```

### Pull Requests

- Keep PRs small and focused (ideally < 400 lines)
- Write clear PR descriptions
- Link to related issues
- Request reviews from appropriate team members
- Ensure CI passes before merging
- Squash commits when merging
